					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I wrote my own compiler from scratch when I determined my &quot;if in doubt, rewrite&quot; coding style was completely unmaintainable in 6502 assembler. It uses the same allocation strategy as dustmop describes, plus a few special-case optimizers for things like converting live ranges to PHA/PLA pairs where possible.<br /><br />As a proof of concept, I used it for everything in Wrecking Balls. I'm both proud of the fact that it worked and embarassed that it took me less time to write a compiler <em>and</em> make a game with it than it would have to write the final product in ASM. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt=":roll:" title="Rolling Eyes" /></div>

